values:
Oh lawd.

I haven't touched WoW since April, and now I have an extreme urge to play.  Must...avoid...stores...that...sell...timecards...

FFUUUUU

brb Target.

I can't get this song out of my head:

<lj-embed id="5"/>

And in other news, I've been playing too much WoW.  I even ignore the internet for it, oh noes.  And I think it may be making me retarded, because I really really like the new Knight Rider.

So I saw Super High Me. I recommend it to everyone - it's so amazingly good! I liked that it wasn't all Doug Benson not being/being high - you got to see what goes on at dispensaries and whatnot. If you're at all interested in medical marijuana rights, the effects of marijuana on humans, or stand-up comedians, you should definitely try to get to a screening of it.

I was thinking about "The High Five'n White Guys" today, so I've spent my day watching clips from Almost Live! on YouTube.

It's been a very productive day here at Casa de Nerd.

Fuck you, Google Image Search.

Looking up "where in the world is carmen sandiego" (I didn't actually use quotes ... maybe that was the problem) gave me many images, mostly not related to Carmen Sandiego.  The best ones were a screenshot from "Secretary," Brian Peppers, and what appeared to be a merkin.

What.  The.  Fuck.

Martin, a gift to you:

<lj-embed id="2" />

So I'm cleaning my laundry room today, and I wanted to listen to something good while I'm doing it.  Glancing quickly at my music, I misread "Sand in the Vaseline" as "Sand in the Vagina."

The end.

Yes.

So I hate to be the sort of person who is easily swayed by advertising, but I just saw this ad, and it's pretty much destroyed the tiny sliver of want that I had for a PlayStation 3.  Fuck you, Sony, and your scary-ass ads.

NationStates "NationStates is a nation simulation game created by Max Barry and based loosely on his novel Jennifer Government." I'm a little in love with this game right now. The only problem I have with it is that it moves really, really slowly. I mean, I've bumped my recieving of issues up to the maximum (2 per day), but it's still all pokey.

In honor of today's date, I present to you selections from The Devil's Dictionary, by Ambrose Bierce. BENEVOLENCE, n. Subscribing five dollars toward the relief of one's aged grandfather in the alms house, and publishing it in the newspaper. BRIDE, n. A woman with a fine prospect of happiness behind her. CHRISTIAN, n. One who believes that the New Testament is a divinely inspired book admirably suited to the spiritual needs of his neighbor. One who follows the teachings of Christ in so far as they are not inconsistent with a life of sin. CONCEIT, n. Self-respect in one whom we dislike. CONGRATULATION, n. The civility of envy. DEPRAVED, p.p. The moral condition of a gentleman who holds the opposite opinion. DISOBEDIENCE, n. The silver lining to the cloud of servitude. EVANGELIST, n. A bearer of good tidings, particularly (in a religious sense) such as assure us of our own salvation and the damnation of our neighbors. FRAUD, n. The life of commerce, the soul of religion, the bait of courtship and the basis of political power. HEAVEN, n. A place where the wicked cease from troubling you with talk of their personal affairs, and the good listen with attention while you expound your own. JEALOUS, adj. Unduly concerned about the preservation of that which can be lost only if not worth keeping. LAWYER, n. One skilled in circumvention of the law. MAN, n. An animal so lost in rapturous contemplation of what he thinks he is as to overlook what he indubitably ought to be. His chief occupation is extermination of other animals and his own species, which, however, multiplies with such insistent rapidity as to infest the whole habitable earth and Canada. NEIGHBOR, n. One whom we are commanded to love as ourselves, and who does all he knows how to make us disobedient. PATRIOT, n. One to whom the interests of a part seem superior to those of the whole. The dupe of statesmen and the tool of conquerers. POLITENESS, n. The most acceptable hypocrisy. PREROGATIVE, n. A sovereign's right to do wrong. PUBLIC, n. The negligible factor in problems of legislation. RELIGION, n. A daughter of Hope and Fear, explaining to Ignorance the nature of the Unknowable. REPRESENTATIVE, n. A gentleman who looks after the interests of his constituents - when they don't conflict with his own. SCRUPLE, n. A word that is falling into disuse as expressing an idea that no longer exists. SELF-ESTEEM, n. An erroneous appraisement. VOTE, n. The instrument and symbol of a freeman's power to make a fool of himself and a wreck of his country.
